Media notes: Audio of calls, given while settling on branches of a honeysuckle (Lonicera) at sunset. Recordings that focus on SWWA calls are much rarer than those of songs.
Observation Details:
Continuing Kevin Powers find. 
 
 Edit: At 8:04 PM, the storm passed, the wind subsided, and the Swainson’s Warbler emerged to call and sing again as he settled onto a honeysuckle branch - perhaps his roosting location for the night.
 
 At 7:24 PM, this SWWA sang several times from the previously described location. This was following nearly two hours of no singing from him. I have a recording of his songs. Sharon Bauer and Gary Zenitsky also heard him sing during this time.
